                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Migraine can be a debilitating disease.&lt;div>1&lt;/div> It affects people in every corner of the world&lt;div>1&lt;/div>, touching family and communities in ways that are difficult to convey. That’s why AbbVie is partnering with the migraine community, advocates and policymakers to make known the true cost.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block>
                <block_1
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
                    filter="custom-title"
                    language="none"
                    model="custom-title"
                    modelFields="[title,titleType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Title"
                    title="Living With Migraine"
                    titleType="h5"/>
                <block_2
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Antonia Cancino from Chile has been living with migraine for more than two decades – since she was 8 years old. Her journey to get help relief mirrors that of many patients: long and full of hurdles.&lt;/p>&lt;p>At first, she struggled to convince doctors that she was experiencing her symptoms. “My mother was a migraine sufferer,” she explained. “They said that I was copying her, that I was imitating her symptoms. Maybe I was not having that pain.” That doubt – even from medical professionals – is something experienced by many migraine patients.&lt;/p>&lt;p>Even after finding a doctor who would treat her as a pediatric patient, she spent 10 years dealing with different treatments and side effects before finding something that worked for her. “I saw that this type of medicine was [in Chile] for more than 30 years. And no one [told me] that they exist,” she said.&lt;/p>&lt;p>Many health care providers and patients are not aware that migraine-specific treatments exist in their country.&lt;div>2&lt;/div> What’s more, even after learning of these treatments, it can be difficult to access those therapies. Antonia’s treatment, for example, was not covered by insurance, which meant she had to pay out-of-pocket.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_2>
                <block_3
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
                    filter="custom-title"
                    language="none"
                    model="custom-title"
                    modelFields="[title,titleType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Title"
                    title="Barriers to Treatment"
                    titleType="h5"/>
                <block_4
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>For neurologist Mario Peres, Antonia’s story is common. Dr. Peres is both the founder of the São Paulo Headache Center and president of the International Headache Society. He sees firsthand the devastating impact migraine can have on patients.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_4>
                <block_5
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    attributionImage="https://delivery-p157365-e1665873.adobeaemcloud.com/adobe/assets/urn:aaid:aem:d525445d-aa2b-470a-9f4f-98f4017f00a8/as/mario-peres-headshot.jpg"
                    attributionImageMimeType="image/unknown"
                    attributionName="Dr. Mario Peres"
                    attributionRole="Neurologist"
                    backgroundImageAlt="\0"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_contentAlignment="quote-align-none"
                    classes_contentWidth="quote-content-col-none"
                    classes_theme="quote-none"
                    customClass="\0"
                    id="\0"
                    language="quote-standard,quote-h4"
                    model="quote"
                    modelFields="[quoteVariant,quotation,attributionName,attributionRole,attributionImage,attributionImageMimeType,quoteFragment,backgroundImage,backgroundImageAlt,backgroundImageMimeType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Quote"
                    quotation="&lt;p>If we understand the burden that migraine imposes onto patients, then we will understand how much this disorder has to be addressed in public health.&lt;/p>"
                    quoteVariant="quote-standard"/>
                <block_6
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>The socioeconomic burden of migraine is comparable to conditions like cardiovascular diseases and diabetes&lt;div>3&lt;/div>, but treatment options are hard to access in much of the world.2 Dr. Peres sees the issue as being twofold: “It’s important to have the diagnosis. It’s important to have access to treatment.”&lt;/p>&lt;p>Part of this is because of the stigma surrounding migraine. According to a recent study from the European Migraine &amp;#x26; Headache Alliance, 93% of migraine sufferers believe that their condition is misunderstood by the general public.&lt;div>4&lt;/div> In both health care and workplace settings, they feel their symptoms are minimized or even dismissed.&lt;div>4&lt;/div>&lt;/p>&lt;p>This stigma compounds the problems for migraine sufferers. According to the study:&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;ul> &lt;li>73% feel health care providers lack understanding of their experience &lt;div>4&lt;/div>&lt;/li> &lt;li>35% of severe migraine patients said they’re embarrassed to seek medical advice &lt;div>4&lt;/div>&lt;/li> &lt;/ul>&lt;/p>&lt;p>Migraine advocates like Dr. Peres agree there is more to be done to support patients. “We have to improve those indicators by advocacy, by health care provider education, by [increasing] access to medications and other treatments,” he said.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_6>
                <block_7
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
                    filter="custom-title"
                    language="none"
                    model="custom-title"
                    modelFields="[title,titleType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Custom Title"
                    title="The Hidden Cost"
                    titleType="h5"/>
                <block_8
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>So, what is that cost? To find out, the WifOR Institute* (a German-based independent economic research institute) worked with international partners to study the socioeconomic burden of various conditions, including migraine. Looking at the data over a 10-year period, the results were eye-opening:&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;ul> &lt;li>Across countries in Europe, Asia and Latin America, the socioeconomic burden of migraine represented about 1.2% to 2% of the annual GDP from 2011-2022. &lt;div>3,5,6&lt;/div>&lt;/li> &lt;li>Migraine was the leading disease with the highest socioeconomic burden compared to other diseases in Brazil, Colombia and Peru. &lt;div>6&lt;/div>&lt;/li> &lt;li>Countries like Mexico, Chile, Colombia, Costa Rica and Ecuador faced an average socioeconomic burden of 1.2%, reaching 1.6% in Brazil and 1.8% in Argentina. &lt;div>6&lt;/div>&lt;/li> &lt;/ul>&lt;/p>&lt;p>This represents billions of dollars lost due to disability and productivity declines.&lt;div>6&lt;/div>&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_8>
                <block_9
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analyticsInteractionId="\0"
                    blockId="\0"
                    caption="\0"
                    classes_commonCustomClass="\0"
                    clickBehavior="_self"
                    displayCaptionBelowImage="false"
